The paper is about improving convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed algorithm involves adding a feedback layer to the CNN, which is a form of recurrent neural network (RNN) and thus could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The emphasis on boosting performance based on previous predictions suggests a focus on optimization and training methods, which could also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves object classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as computer vision.
